      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">13.005</ph> List of laws inapplicable
to contracts and subcontracts at or below the simplified acquisition threshold.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d726e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d747e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  The following laws are inapplicable
to all contracts and subcontracts (if otherwise applicable to subcontracts)
at or below the simplified acquisition threshold pursuant to <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 1905</xref>:
               </p>
               <ol id="d726e26" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d747e19" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section8102&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 8102</xref>(a)(1)
(Drug-Free Workplace), except for individuals.
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d747e26" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section2306&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 2306</xref>(b)
and <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section3901&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 3901</xref>(b)
(Contract Clause Regarding Contingent Fees).
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d747e36" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section2313&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 2313</xref> and <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section4706&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 4706</xref> (Authority
to Examine Books and Records of Contractors).
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d747e46" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section2402&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 2402</xref> and <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section4704&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 4704</xref> (Prohibition
on Limiting Subcontractors Direct Sales to the United States).
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d747e56" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                        <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title15-section631&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C. 631</xref> note
(HUBZone Act of 1997), except for <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title15-section657a&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C. 657a</xref>(b)(2)(B),
which is optional for the agencies subject to the requirements of
the Act.
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d747e66" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(6)</ph>
                        <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title31-section1354&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">31 U.S.C. 1354</xref>(a)
(Limitation on use of appropriated funds for contracts with entities
not meeting veterans employment reporting requirements).
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d747e73" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(7)</ph>
                        <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title22-section2593e&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">22 U.S.C. 2593e</xref> (Measures
Against Persons Involved in Activities that Violate Arms Control
Treaties or Agreements with the United States). (The requirement
at <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title22-section2593e&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">22 U.S.C. 2593e</xref>(c)(3)(B)
to provide a certification does not apply).
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d747e83" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> The Federal
Acquisition Regulatory (FAR) Council will include any law enacted
after October 13,1994, that sets forth policies, procedures, requirements,
or restrictions for the acquisition of property or services, on
the list set forth in paragraph (a) of this section. The FAR Council
may make exceptions when it determines in writing that it is in
the best interest of the Government that the enactment should apply
to contracts or subcontracts not greater than the simplified acquisition threshold.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d747e88" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> The provisions
of paragraph (b) of this section do not apply to laws that-</p>
               <ol id="d726e189" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d747e94" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Provide
for criminal or civil penalties; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d747e99" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Specifically
state that notwithstanding the language of <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 1905</xref>, the
enactment will be applicable to contracts or subcontracts in amounts
not greater than the simplified acquisition threshold.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d747e107" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph> Any individual
may petition the Administrator, Office of Federal Procurement Policy
(OFPP), to include any applicable provision of law not included
on the list set forth in paragraph (a) of this section unless the
FAR Council has already determined in writing that the law is applicable.
The Administrator, OFPP, will include the law on the list in paragraph (a)
of this section unless the FAR Council makes a determination that
it is applicable within 60 days of receiving the petition.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
